party material.name: Monopoly Fortnite
party material.descr: Capture locations, battle your opponents and escape the storm to survive and win the game in this exciting Fortnite version of the Monopoly game! Inspired by the popular video game, Monopoly Fortnite also includes video game locations and Treasure Chest objects. Instead of Monopoly money, players gain health points. Decide on one of 27 styles to choose your character before starting the game. Use Treasure Chest objects and action dice to battle your opponents! Action allows you to collect health points, build walls and damage your opponents. Treasure Chest cards give you epic items to make these actions even more powerful! When you pass the STARTING point, you start the storm! Avoid the storm or you will lose health points! As in the Fortnite video game, the last player standing wins the game! Includes: playground, 27 character cards with plastic stands, 15 Storm cards, 16 location cards, 16 Treasure Chests cards, 8 Wall cards, number 1 dice, 1 action dice and stickers, 110 Health Points stamps, and game guide. MONOPOLY FORTNITE BOX GAME - Fortnite fans! This version of Monopoly is inspired by the popular Fortnite video game! This time it's not what you have, it's how long you survive! FOR FORTNITE FANS - Seize locations, battle opponents and escape the storm in Monopoly Fortnite board game for 2 to 7 players. The last player standing wins the game. FORTNITE LOCATIONS AND HEALTH POINTS - The Monopoly Fortnite board game features well-known locations from the video game instead of plots. Players try to earn health point stamps instead of Monopoly money to stay in the game. BATTLE OPPONENTS - Use Treasure Chest items and action dice to battle your opponents in this fun board game for Monopoly and Fortnite fans 13+. CHOOSE A STYLE - The game includes 27 Fortnite outfits with plastic stands, and players can choose to play in their favorite style. Age 13 and up, played with 2 to 7 players.

party material.name: Monopoly Speed
party material.descr: Monopoly Don't have much time? No problem! You can play Monopoly Speed ​​in less than 10 minutes! In this version of Monopoly, everyone can roll the dice and buy properties at the same time, so players don't have to wait their turn. Throughout 4 rounds, players race against the timer to buy, trade and sell properties faster than ever before. The timer counts down at each buy and trade stage and there is no break between stages. There are two Starting points on the playground and players can exit Jail for free each time. The Monopoly Speed ​​box is a great choice for family game night, parties with friends, and breaks during the day. • Contents: playing field, 4 pawns, 4 dice, 28 Title Deed cards, 16 Chance cards, 12 Public Fund cards, deck of money (150 M1000 banknotes) and game guide. • PLAY IN LESS THAN 10 MINUTES: Want to play Monopoly but don't have much time? You can finish Monopoly Speed ​​in less than 10 minutes. • PLAYED IN TIMED ROUNDS: This fast-paced Monopoly board game is played in rounds. The timer counts down during the buy and trade phases of each round. • EVERYONE BUY AT THE SAME TIME: No need to wait your turn! Each player has a pawn and a matching dice. In the buying stages, everyone rolls the dice at the same time and buys property. • SUPER SPEED TRADING: Chance cards assist players in the trading phase. Get a bonus at the end of the game with Community Fund cards. • FUN FAMILY GAME: Play Monopoly Speed ​​whenever you want a quick game! With this great game, you can get your family and friends together even when your time is limited. • For ages 8 and above. • Played with 2 to 4 players. • Operates with 3 x 1.5 V AAA alkaline thin batteries. (Batteries are not included in the box.)

party material.name: Detective Jungle Brain Game Hobby Education World
party material.descr:
Detective Jungle Brain Teaser Boxed games. Hobby Education World.
300 forest animals are hiding on this game board. Could you be the first to spot the giraffe or even the giraffe louse? Get a chip in the box and see who can find that animal first!
Simple to understand but addictive, this game will delight adults and children alike and provide hours of family fun.
INGREDIENTS
1 double-sided game board
300 game stamps
Bell
PLAY
2+ players 5++ Group game
GAINS:
Speed, Reflex, Visual perception, Visual attention
The cards in the Jungle Game are stacked on top of each other so that their backs are visible. The shapes are then placed in the middle. The bell is placed in the middle where everyone can reach it. The card is turned over, starting with the top card. The first to see the shapes on the playing card on the floor, press the bell and show the shapes. You have to be careful because there are several versions of all the pictures. What you see first may not be correct.
For example, you may encounter the crocodile picture you see both with and without a tail. In this unique safari, the one who sees the cards correctly and presses the bell the fastest gets the chip and wins the game.
Are you ready for a unique safari tour?

party material.name: Master Detective Boxed Mind Game Hobby World
party material.descr:
Master Detective Boxed Mind Game Hobby World
70 Game Cards
1 Pcs Ring
Printed Cardboard Floor
How is the game played?
The cards in the Master Detective game are stacked on top of each other so that their backs are visible. Then, printed figures of 16x22 cm length, consisting of 9 parts, are placed in the middle to form 68x48 cm. The bell is placed in the middle where everyone can reach it. The card is turned over, starting with the top card in order. The first to see the shapes on the playing card on the floor, press the bell and show the shapes.
You need to be careful. Because all my paintings have several different endings. The first figure you see may not be correct. For example, you can see the cat picture you see both with and without a tail. If there are three shapes on the card, 3 points are added, if there are 2 shapes, 2 points, if there are 1 shapes, 1 point is added.
If the bell is pressed incorrectly, the game continues. The person who hits the bell incorrectly will not receive a minus point.
Whoever collects the most scorecards wins the game.
